VALUES
(42, 10, 22, 40, 28, 18, 18, NULL, 'Authority of the Son', 'This connection highlights the authority given to Jesus by the Father. Both passages emphasize the power and knowledge shared between the Father and the Son.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 22, 63, 1, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Father and Son', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son. Luke 10:22 highlights the exclusive knowledge of the Father and Son, while 2 John 1:9 states that one must abide in the doctrine of Christ to have both the Father and the Son.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 22, 62, 5, 20, 20, 'who the Son is, but the Father', 'Understanding of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the knowledge of the Son and the relationship with the Father. Luke 10:22 highlights that the Son reveals the Father, while 1 John 5:20 states that the Son gives understanding to know the true God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 23, 40, 13, 16, 17, 'Blessed are the eyes which see', 'Blessed Eyes and Ears', 'Both passages emphasize the blessing of seeing and hearing spiritual truths. They highlight the privilege of the disciples in perceiving what many prophets longed to witness.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 24, 43, 8, 56, 56, 'those things which ye see', 'Desire to See and Rejoice', 'This connection highlights the longing of prophets and kings to witness the fulfillment of God''s promises, as expressed in Luke. Similarly, John emphasizes Abraham''s joy in seeing the arrival of Jesus, indicating a shared theme of anticipation and fulfillment.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 24, 58, 11, 13, 13, 'desired to see those things', 'Desire for Promises and Faith', 'This connection highlights the longing of prophets and kings to see the promises of God, as expressed in both passages. Luke 10:24 mentions those who desired to see, while Hebrews 11:13 speaks of those who saw the promises afar off in faith.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 24, 58, 11, 39, 39, 'those things which ye see', 'Desire for Revelation', 'This connection highlights the longing of prophets and kings to witness the fulfillment of God''s promises, as noted in Luke. Hebrews reflects on those who had faith but did not receive the promise, suggesting a continuity in the theme of unfulfilled longing.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 24, 60, 1, 10, 12, 'desired to see those things which ye see', 'Desire of Prophets and Kings', 'Both passages emphasize the longing of prophets to understand the salvation that is now revealed. Luke highlights that many have desired to see and hear what the disciples experience, while 1 Peter notes that prophets searched diligently for the grace that has come to believers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 25, 40, 22, 34, 39, 'what shall I do to inherit eternal life?', 'Connection of Eternal Life and Love', 'Both passages emphasize the inquiry of a lawyer seeking guidance on fundamental aspects of the law. The SOURCE verse asks about inheriting eternal life, while the TARGET passage discusses the greatest commandments, which are essential to living a life that aligns with God''s will.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 25, 42, 18, 18, 18, 'what shall I do to inherit eternal life?', 'Inquiry about Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the question of what one must do to inherit eternal life. This connection highlights a common theme of seeking understanding about salvation.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 25, 44, 16, 30, 31, NULL, 'Inquiry about Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize a question regarding salvation, with the lawyer asking about inheriting eternal life and the jailer inquiring about being saved. This connection highlights the consistent theme of seeking assurance of salvation in the New Testament.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 25, 40, 19, 16, 19, 'what shall I do to inherit eternal life?', 'Inquiry about Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize a question about inheriting eternal life. They highlight the importance of following commandments as a response to this inquiry.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 25, 48, 3, 18, 18, 'inherit eternal life', 'Inheritance and Eternal Life', 'This connection highlights the concept of ''inheritance'' as it relates to eternal life and the promise given to Abraham. Both passages emphasize the importance of divine promise over the law in attaining eternal life.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 25, 42, 11, 45, 46, 'what shall I do to inherit eternal life?', 'Lawyers and Burdens', 'This connection highlights the role of lawyers in both passages, where the first lawyer seeks guidance on eternal life, and the second lawyer responds to Jesus'' rebuke of their burdensome teachings. Both passages emphasize the responsibilities and challenges associated with the legalistic interpretations of faith.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 26, 23, 8, 20, 20, 'what is written in the law', 'Connection Between Law and Testimony', 'This connection highlights the importance of the law in both passages. Luke 10:26 asks about what is written in the law, while Isaiah 8:20 emphasizes adherence to the law and testimony as a source of light.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 26, 45, 10, 5, 5, 'what is written in the law', 'Connection of Law and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the law and righteousness. Both passages emphasize the importance of adhering to the law for life and righteousness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 26, 48, 3, 21, 22, 'what is written in the law', 'Connection Between Law and Faith', 'This connection highlights the role of the law in understanding sin and righteousness. Both passages emphasize the importance of the law in relation to faith and the promise of Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 26, 45, 3, 19, 19, 'what is written in the law', 'Connection Between Law and Guilt', 'This connection highlights the role of the law in revealing human guilt. In Luke, the inquiry about the law points to its significance, while Romans emphasizes that the law exposes the guilt of all under it.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 26, 48, 3, 12, 13, 'What is written in the law?', 'Connection Between Law and Faith', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the law and its fulfillment in Christ. Both passages emphasize the importance of the law and the consequences of not adhering to it, as well as Christ''s role in redeeming from its curse.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 27, 40, 22, 37, 40, 'Thou shalt love the Lord thy God', 'Connection of Love Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the command to love God and neighbor. They articulate the same core principles of love, highlighting their significance in the law.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 27, 41, 12, 30, 31, 'Thou shalt love the Lord thy God', 'Love Commandments Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the command to love God and neighbor. They share identical phrasing regarding loving God with all one''s heart, soul, mind, and strength.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 27, 5, 6, 5, 5, NULL, 'Love for God and Neighbor', 'Both passages emphasize the command to love God with all one''s heart, soul, and strength. Luke expands on this by including the love for one''s neighbor, highlighting the interconnectedness of these commandments.', 'theme', 0.937, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 27, 45, 13, 9, 9, NULL, 'Love Your Neighbor Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the command to love one''s neighbor as oneself. Luke 10:27 introduces this principle, while Romans 13:9 summarizes it as encompassing other commandments.', 'theme', 0.748, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 27, 3, 19, 18, 18, NULL, 'Connection of Love for Neighbors', 'Both passages emphasize the command to love one''s neighbor as oneself. This connection highlights the continuity of the principle of love in both the Old and New Testaments.', 'theme', 0.692, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 27, 5, 30, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Love for God', 'Both passages emphasize loving the Lord with all one''s heart and soul. Luke 10:27 echoes the command found in Deuteronomy 30:6, highlighting the importance of total devotion to God.', 'theme', 0.657, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 27, 59, 2, 8, 8, NULL, 'Connection of Love Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the command to love one''s neighbor as oneself. Luke 10:27 presents this as part of the greatest commandments, while James 2:8 refers to it as the royal law.', 'theme', 0.594, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 28, 26, 20, 11, 11, 'thou shalt live', 'Connection of Life Through Obedience', 'Both passages emphasize the principle that obedience to God''s commands leads to life. In Luke, the affirmation of doing right results in life, while Ezekiel states that living by God''s statutes also brings life.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 28, 3, 18, 5, 5, 'thou shalt live', 'Connection of Life Through Obedience', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of living through adherence to God''s commandments. Luke 10:28 reflects the idea that doing right leads to life, paralleling Leviticus 18:5''s assertion that keeping statutes results in life.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 28, 40, 19, 17, 17, NULL, 'Connection on Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of keeping commandments to attain eternal life. They highlight the relationship between obedience and living, suggesting that following God''s commandments is essential for spiritual life.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 28, 16, 9, 29, 29, 'thou shalt live', 'Connection of Life Through Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of living through adherence to God''s commandments. Both passages emphasize that obedience to the law is linked to life, as seen in ''thou shalt live'' and ''if a man do, he shall live in them.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
